Linux and Open Source Genius Guide Volume 02 2013


English | 260 pages | True PDF | 50.9 Mb




Designed for Linux professionals and IT decision makers, this book provides the best in tutorials, features, information and inspiration to help GNU/Linux users run their systems more effectively. The book also comes with step-by-step guides to developing for both established and emerging platforms such as iPhone, Android and the Palm Pre. Over 200 pages of Tutorials.
discover the power of Linux Get the low-down on the key areas of Linux use and development, including a comprehensive guide to Python. Start developing your own apps and services, including the popular mobile platforms iPhone and Android
